## 4. Timing System (LOCKED)

| Token              | Duration | Use Case                                             |
|--------------------|---------:|------------------------------------------------------|
| `DUR.micro`        | 180ms    | Hover state changes, focus rings, cursor adapt       |
| `DUR.quick`        | 380ms    | Small reveals, button reactions, label fades         |
| `DUR.standard`     | 720ms    | Default content reveal (image, paragraph, heading)   |
| `DUR.cinematic`    | 1200ms   | Hero element reveal, chapter title entry             |
| `DUR.epic`         | 1800ms   | Chapter transitions, full-bleed dissolves            |
| `DUR.glacial`      | 2600ms   | Atmospheric ambient loops, ultra-slow drifts        |

```ts
export const DUR = {
  micro: 0.18, quick: 0.38, standard: 0.72,
  cinematic: 1.2, epic: 1.8, glacial: 2.6,
} as const;
```

### Constraints
- **Never** use durations between tokens (no 0.5s, no 1s). Snap to the dictionary.
- **Never** animate longer than `DUR.glacial` (2.6s) for a single property.
- **Never** animate shorter than `DUR.micro` (180ms) — anything faster reads as a glitch.

---

## 5. Stagger System

Stagger creates **rhythm**. Treat it as musical.

```ts
export const STAGGER = {
  tight:    0.04,  // letters in a word, dots in a list
  editorial: 0.08, // words in a phrase, image grid
  scene:    0.16,  // sibling sections, paragraph blocks
  chapter:  0.32,  // major elements between chapters
} as const;
```

### Rules
- Stagger groups must contain **3–9 elements**. More than 9 → break into sub-staggers.
- For text reveal, stagger by **word**, not by character (character-stagger reads as "techy").
  - Exception: short oversized titles (≤3 words) may stagger by character with `tight`.
- Stagger direction defaults to **start** (top→bottom, left→right). For dramatic emphasis, use `from: "center"`.

---

## 6. Reveal System

All reveals follow the **STRATEGICLAND reveal grammar**:

```ts
// Default content reveal
gsap.from(target, {
  yPercent: 8,        // never more than 12, never less than 4
  opacity: 0,
  filter: "blur(8px)",// optional, atmospheric reveals only
  duration: DUR.standard,
  ease: EASE.gsap.cinematic,
  stagger: STAGGER.editorial,
});
```

### Constraints
- Translation: `yPercent` only, range **4–12%**. Never `xPercent` for reveals (reads as carousel).
- Scale: forbidden for reveals (use opacity + translate). Scale is reserved for image treatments.
- Rotation: forbidden except for ambient atmospheric motion ≤ 0.6deg.
- Blur reveal (`filter: blur(8px)→blur(0)`): allowed only for hero / chapter establishing shots. Cost: GPU layer.
- Always reveal **once** per scroll direction. No re-reveal on re-scroll up.

---

## 7. Scroll-Linked Motion

- Scroll-scrubbed timelines must use `scrub: 1` (1-second smoothing) — **never** `scrub: true` (instant).
- Scroll-velocity-driven values must clamp: `gsap.utils.clamp(min, max, value)`. No raw velocity → reads as motion sickness.
- Parallax depth: max **3 layers** per scene. Background `0.3x`, midground `0.6x`, foreground `1x` (native).
- Parallax displacement: max **15% of viewport height** total travel.
- Always integrate with Lenis: subscribe via `lenis.on("scroll", ...)`, never via native `window.addEventListener("scroll")`.

---

## 8. Inertia & Physics Principles

- All draggable / momentum elements obey **inertial decay** (Lenis or `gsap.InertiaPlugin`-style logic).
- No element instantly stops. Every motion has a **falloff tail ≥ 200ms**.
- Magnetic cursor effects (see `interaction-system.mdc`) use **damped lerp**: `lerp factor 0.08–0.12`.
- Mouse-driven parallax intensity max: **24px translate** for hero elements, **8px** for body.

---

## 9. Layered Motion Hierarchy

A single scene may compose motion in **at most 4 layers**:

1. **Atmospheric** — slow ambient (grain drift, light leak, WebGL noise) → `breath` ease, ≥`DUR.glacial`.
2. **Structural** — main reveal (hero text, image) → `cinematic` ease, `DUR.cinematic`.
3. **Detail** — captions, secondary text → `cinematic` ease, `DUR.standard`, staggered after structural.
4. **Reactive** — pointer-driven (parallax, magnetic) → `lerp 0.1`, no easing.

Layers must enter in **order: 1 → 2 → 3**. Layer 4 is always-on. Never animate two structural elements simultaneously without stagger.

---

## 10. Forbidden Motion Patterns

- ❌ Bouncy, elastic, back-out, overshooting eases.
- ❌ Continuous looping rotation on UI elements (decorative spinners).
- ❌ Pulsing CTAs, "breathing" buttons, scale-on-hover ≥ 1.05.
- ❌ Carousel auto-advance.
- ❌ Marquee tickers (unless explicitly editorial chapter device, never decorative).
- ❌ Cursor trails / particle followers.
- ❌ Splash screens with progress bars (use atmospheric intro instead).
- ❌ Hover-triggered Lottie / SVG morph "fun" interactions.
- ❌ Animating `top`, `left`, `width`, `height`, `margin`. Use `transform` and `opacity` only.
- ❌ `will-change` set permanently. Set on enter, clear on complete.

---

## 11. Implementation Standards

### File location
- All reusable motion utilities live in `lib/motion/`.
- Per-component motion in a co-located `<component>.motion.ts`.
- Never inline > 8 lines of GSAP timeline inside a JSX file.

### GSAP context isolation
- All GSAP work in React must use `gsap.context()` and clean up in effect return.
  ```ts
  useEffect(() => {
    const ctx = gsap.context(() => {
      gsap.from(".reveal", { /* ... */ });
    }, scopeRef);
    return () => ctx.revert();
  }, []);
  ```
- Use `useGSAP` from `@gsap/react` if/when added to the stack — preferred over manual context.

### Reduced motion
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` globally via a `useReducedMotion()` hook.
- In reduced mode: opacity reveals only, no translate, no blur, no scrub. Duration capped at `DUR.quick`.
- Never disable navigation/transition logic — only soften it.

### SSR / Hydration
- Never animate during the first paint. Wait for `useLayoutEffect` and Lenis ready event.
- Initial state must be **the final state** (so SSR snapshot is correct), then GSAP `from()` to move backward → forward.

---

## 12. Motion Review Checklist

Before merging any motion work, confirm:
- [ ] Eases come from `EASE` dictionary.
- [ ] Durations come from `DUR` dictionary.
- [ ] Stagger comes from `STAGGER` dictionary.
- [ ] No animated `top/left/width/height/margin`.
- [ ] No bouncy/elastic eases.
- [ ] Reduced-motion path tested.
- [ ] GSAP context cleaned up on unmount.
- [ ] Single layer per element (no stacking translate + scale + rotate without reason).
- [ ] If scrubbed, `scrub: 1` minimum.
- [ ] Looks intentional at 0.5x playback (Cmd+Shift+P → "throttle CPU 4x" in DevTools).
